animal.description:
Hi! My name is Pancake. My foster mom thinks I look like a stack of pancakes that has syrup drizzled on them. She’s just jealous of my brindle coat! I am sweeter than actual pancakes though. Giving kisses should be my profession. I love to follow females around, I get nervous when I first meet men. If men are patient and earn my trust I will be their big baby. I love going outside but, must have a really tall fence. I am an athlete and will clear it. I’d prefer to be walked on a leash and wouldn't be great in an apartment. Actually, I’d rather go for a run. I get one daily right now and I will beg you for it. I’d prefer someone who will take me on adventures. I love car rides and being outdoors. I am kennel and potty trained. I must sleep with you at night because I'm such a good snuggler. I also really LOVE little humans. I follow kids everywhere and love to be next to them as much as I can. Do you have some of those? I can't wait to meet you. I get nervous around other dogs. I need to be the only dog in the house, unless there is a dog that is very submissive, and you don’t mind putting in work. I want a family that can be patient and understanding with me. I’d like a family who will spend time teaching me new tricks and furthering my training.

If you are interested in meeting Pancake, please fill out an application via our website at https://therescueproject.net/adoption-application and we will get back to you via email once your application has been reviewed. If you have further questions please feel free to reach out to us at adoptionstrp@gmail.com

Pancake's adoption fee is $200.  This includes age-appropriate vaccines, spay/neuter, microchip, deworm, heartworm testing.

animal.description:
RC is ready to find his forever family, and he wants them to know these 10 things about him:

1.	I am a Bullmastiff, and I’m about 5 years old.

2.	I CAN’T GO TO A HOME THAT DOESN’T HAVE EXTENSIVE GIANT/ GUARDIAN BREED EXPERIENCE. It’s super important that my forever family understands me, and why I do the things that I do.  The people at the Bullpen are very serious about this, and will not consider applications from unqualified individuals.  

3.	Like many dogs of my breed, I can be wary of strangers, and I need to be introduced to new people and visitors slowly.   A busy house is NOT for me.

4.	I have met some of the other Bullpen dogs, and I don’t mind them too much.  If introduced appropriately, I think I would do well in a home that had a large, laid-back female dog (but I also wouldn’t mind being the only pet in the home).

5.	Since I came to rescue, I haven’t spent much time in the company of smaller dogs, but I might be able to live in a house with medium to large sized dogs. My new family just needs to make sure we have a gradual, proper introduction. 

6.	I am interested in the barn cats at the sanctuary in all the wrong ways.  A feline-free home would be the best fit for me.  

7.	I haven’t had much experience with kids, but I’m pretty sure I could live in a home with teenage children, as long as they weren’t too loud or rambunctious.
 
8.	I love to spend time outside, eat bones, play with toys, and sleep on the bed with my foster dad! 

9.	I am housebroken, crate-trained, good on a leash, and I also know basic commands!

10.	 I am current on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm negative, and neutered.  

Ready to give RC the forever home of his dreams?  Fill out our Adoption Application, located at www.bullpenrescue.org under the 'work with us' tab.

**We highly recommend that our potential adopters fill out an online application as soon as possible, as it greatly expedites the process of finding the right dog for your situation.  

Our dogs are available for adoption nationwide but preference is given to adopters willing to do an in-person meeting.  Please understand that our dogs are not adopted on a first-come, first-serve basis, but rather we strive for a "perfect placement" so we know that they will not be failed again.**

animal.description:
THOR - A Handsome, Strong, and Loyal German Shepherd


Can a name 'fit' a dog? We think so in Thor's case. He is a handsomely rugged pure bred adult German Shepherd dog. Thor has a strong personality and lots of energy. Thor enjoys the outdoors, especially going on hikes or even better a nice fenced in backyard to fetch and just have a fun time.  

Thor is very friendly and loyal to the volunteers at Sedona Shepherd. While in our care and at our facility, Thor is comfortable greeting new people, and generally will ignore well mannered large dogs. We keep Thor well socialized and he is comfortable meeting new adults and older children. 

In his prior home, after settling in nicely, Thor did become protective of the household and needed to be properly introduced to visitors.  Once proper introductions are made Thor will accept visitors into a home, especially if they want to play fetch with him. Thor can walk nicely on a leash, though he is strong and when starting out likes to pull. Generally, if another dog ignores Thor, he will do the same. 

Thor will flourish in a home with no other animals and an experienced German Shepherd owner. He is trustworthy in a house, smart, well trained and is looking to bond with his new best friend. We estimate Thor to be about 7 years old.  Because Thor did have a bite incident two years ago when a contractor was visiting his home, he will be adopted out on a bite contract.

At this time we are looking for a foster to adopt situation with Thor.  He has developed an allergy and anti-resistant infection in his ear canal.  Thor will be having an ear ablation surgery on his left ear, covered fully by Sedona Shepherd and our wonderful donors.

PLEASE NOTE: Any foster/adopter MUST have prior German Shepherd experience, must live either in New Jersey, eastern PA or Southern NJ and have no other animals in the house. We will not respond to any inquires that do not meet the above requirements. Thor is an amazing dog who needs to be in the best environment for him.


Sedona Shepherd Sanctuary's mission is to rescue adult and senior German Shepherd and mixes and find them loving homes. All of our dogs are fully vetted, up to date on all their shots

Our adoption area includes New Jersey, Delaware Valley, Manhattan, Southern New York. We may adopt to Connecticut depending on circumstances. Please visit our website at www.sedonashepherd.com.

Sedona

animal.description:
Handsome Marcos is an approximately 2-year-old lab mix looking for a best friend and partner in crime. Marcos is a highly motivated and photogenic guy hoping to find someone who will help continue his training and help him practice all his amazing skills. Marcos is a graduate of a very prestigious board and train program where he learned things like loose-leash walking, sit, down, stay, wait, leave it, bed (place), settle, and recall (come when called). Marcos is very playful but is sometimes unaware of his size and strength. A home with children is probably not the best fit for him. His playful and fun-loving nature needs to be balanced by structure and boundaries. His excellent obedience is the perfect vehicle for the required structure. Marcos needs a confident handler, willing to show him what is expected and then hold him accountable to those expectations. Marcos tends to make impulsive decisions, as do most dogs, so an emphasis on impulse control (through the use of the wait and place commands) will be a must. Marcos would prefer to be the only dog in the home so that he and his new person can focus on continuing his training and building their relationship. However, Marcos is not reactive around other dogs when out and about on walks and such. Marcos will reward anyone willing to help him be the very best dog he can be with a lifetime of loyalty and friendship.

animal.description:
When I first saw you You had sparkle in your eye Like the stars at night High in the sky How I wish That you were mine 'Cause to me You're one of a kind When I look at you It seems so untrue How someone like you Can make me feel the way you do- from 'Sparkle' by Cameo
  You definitely need some Sparkle in your life and we have just the girl to brighten up your world. Sparkle is a 5 
 year old Hound mix weighing 71 lbs. She ended up in the shelter and her previous owners failed her miserably by not reclaiming her. She likely wandered off due to living in a non secured yard/home. This gorgeous girl is already house and crate trained with very good house manners. Sparkle loves everyone she meets big and small, never meets a stranger but will need older kids . She is great with other large  dogs so she will do well with potential doggie family members. We do not recommend a home with cats as she is way too tempted to play chase with them. Sparkle's ideal home will include older kids and a doggie playmate. Sparkle will make your day warm, fuzzy, and of course 'sparkly' when she snuggles up with you on the couch letting you know how very much you are loved and adored. Foster mom says Sparkle likes to sleep right next to her in the bed...comfy and cozy. This adorable girl is eager to please and happy to learn. She has picked up on a few things like sit, down, and shake. Treats make it even better! She will require a secure tall  fenced in yard as she is pretty agile and may attempt to jump a  fence if something strikes her fancy (that would be her Hound genes at work). Foster mom tells us that this is the only bad habit or less desirable behavior she has seen in this otherwise wonderful young lady. She is a joy to be with and great company to have. Sparkle is already spayed, up to date on all vaccinations, current on preventatives, and micro chipped. The only thing missing from Sparkle's life is a forever home and a family who will keep her safe and love her always. She's a one of a kind gal who will be the sparkle in your eyes. No need to wish that she was yours... make it happen cuz there is just no better feeling in the world than having your best friend, Sparkle, by your side

animal.description:
Scamper is a 4 year old, 39 pound beagle mix - probably got some cattle dog in him as well. Yellow and white with a little black. He was rescued from a shelter last year. He came in shy and still is a bit, but he has warmed up a lot. He's enjoyed meeting kids who visit, and he knows how to 'shake'. He loves getting treats and takes them nicely. He should open up even more in a home where he would have one on one attention.
He is house trained, however, we as say that all dogs need a refresher course at their forever homes. He is okay with other dogs.
He is fixed, is chipped, and is up to date on all his shots.
Please find our applications and valuable information under 'Adopt a dog'* on our website: *www.beaglesandbuddies.com* and email your application to beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Let us know your preference of appointment day/time and which dogs you are interested in and we will do our best to accommodate and email you the closest appointment available. Please allow us up to a week to get back to you. Most appointments will be Friday-Sunday, 10 am - 2 pm, for an hour.
*Note bring any other dog/s and the entire family to your meet and greet at B&B.* A complimentary training manual is included with each adoption, authored by terristeuben.com. Check out her website - she is fabulous!
B&B is glad to be open during the pandemic. We know the value and comfort of a loving pet companion and are doing our best to help the dogs and folks who need them. We update our website daily and are always rescuing, vetting, rehabilitating, socializing.
* We are accepting applications for volunteers to spend time with our dogs, hang out, sing/read to the shy ones, walk/toss ball with those who go to the playgrounds; cleaning, office work, gardening, and building/repair projects! *
Are you my furrever family?

For further info on the adoption process, please visit our home page and check out the "Adopt a Dog" section, which has thorough instructions. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and

fully vaccinated before adoption; they have been wormed, bathed, socialized, walked daily and much loved; each adoptee leaves with a leash, collar, and all medical records.

Our prices are higher than the shelters' because we nurse the dogs through their illnesses and get them needed surgeries and dentals. We also spend time socializing. Furthermore, unlike shelters, rescues do not get financial aid from the government and must rely on donations, grants, and adoption fees. Our fees for adults start at $150 and go up to $750. The higher end is for our most in demand dogs, such as young beagles and other purebred dogs. The lower end is for dogs who have been here a while. For puppies, we may go beyond this and charge $1000. The good news is that, because rescues fall under the "charity" category, the fees for our dogs are officially donations and are therefore tax deductible. You can think of it as donating to a worthy cause and getting a dog in return!

Sponsor Me

Beagles & Buddies must find ways to raise money so we can continue saving dogs. Your tax-deductible donation keeps our rescue kennel operating!

Hours

Friday: 10 am to 3 pm

Saturday: 10 am to 3 pm

Sunday: 10 am to 3 pm

Monday: CLOSED

Tuesday: CLOSED

Wednesday: CLOSED

Thursday: CLOSED



Weekday appointments may be available. We are a small staff and do our best to accommodate your needs. **Note that during COVID, we are not holding open houses on any day. Please email us for an appointment and include your application (found on our website, beaglesandbuddies.com, under "Forms"). Most appointments will be Friday through Sunday, though other days may also be available. We usually schedule one appointment per hour. Allow 1-2 hours for your appointment. Please look at our website and make a list of one or more dogs that you would like to see.

Contacting Us

If you have a question about adopting, giving up a dog, boarding, or volunteering, please visit the appropriate tabs on our
home page.

For more specific questions, call 626-444-9664 (please leave a voicemail if no answer) or email at beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Note that
Emailing
is always preferred!

Thanks!

animal.description:
Grandma is a 9-year-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, 4dx/heartworm tested, and spayed/neutered. This dog is also tested with other dogs, kennel-trained, and housebroken. We would love for you to meet this dog and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: We typically host weekly Saturday adoption events. In order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment. Appointments are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, private adoption appointments are only offered for individual animals.

As always, our foster homes are happy to speak to approved applicants prior to meeting up to ensure compatible matches. Furthermore, they are happy to accommodate video chat, text messages, pictures, etc. to reduce in-person contact.

While our adoption appointment objects are thoroughly disinfected before and after use (writing pens, clipboard, tables), adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees can also be completed electronically (which is preferred). Private appointments will be scheduled in intervals to avoid large gatherings of people.***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

Thank you for choosing adoption! If you would like more information on our organization please visit our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org.

animal.description:
POOKIE is looking for her forever home.  She lost the one home she ever knew  due to death, illness, and eviction.  She and her sister, STELLA,  need to find a new home together.  Stella and Pookie have lived together pretty much all their lives. Pookie is 8 yrs. old and is a great dog who will have you laughing with her ways and shining spirit.

If you can't adopt but are interested in fostering, please contact us ASAP.

Pookie and Stella are housetrained and are not big barkers.  They do fine home alone with each other for company once acclimated.  Stella, in particular needs someone who can get her out for walks/hikes, but Pookie loves a walk as well.  She's quite the explorer.  They also both love sitting on the couch with their person and watching TV.  Pookie is a little bit cautious when meeting new people, but warms up quickly.  Pookie loves pets and being held once she knows you. Pookie likes to bark at new dogs, but once she knows they're friendly, she's fine.  See STELLA's separate posting for more pictures of her. 

POOKIE is gentle and sweet and a big fan of cuddles and kisses.  The girls have never lived with kids, but did live near a school and were fine with the kids, though Pookie's sister Stella could knock over a youngster with her exuberance.  Older kids should be fine.  They have never lived with a cat, so without is probably easiest.  Pookie and Stella would love to find a new home together, ideally with a yard as that's what they're used to.
animal.name: Pookie

The girls really like meeting kids when out on their walks.

animal.description:
Rocky's foster mom calls him Rockstar, and for good reason. He's a
handsome Llewellyn boy with a sweet face that will melt your heart.
And like some rockstars, he does have his quirks. But we're sure that
in the right home, 9 year young Rocky will flourish as a companion and family
member. He's house-trained, adores people and so wants to be adored in
return. He is looking for a home where he has a female caretaker and his person will be around most of the time.

He's had a bit of a tough go. He was initially a hunting ranch reject. Hunting is definitely not his thing, he doesn’t even really like to be outside for very long and he hates to get his feet wet. After the hunting ranch he was in a home for six years before he was released to SWESR because his family was not able or willing to deal with his skin allergies. His allergies are under control with diet and allergy medication.

Rocky’s doggy social skills are not great. He requires controlled/slow intros with other dogs and is not a candidate for dog parks. He lacks confidence and would not be good in a home with dominate male dogs or sick/weaker dogs. He’ll be best as an only dog or with a calm dog that leaves him alone. He is ok with inside cats, no outside cats.

What Rocky most needs is a stable environment and consistent loving
attention to help him realize that he's OK and that he belongs! He will always have some anxiety but after what he has been through, coupled with the sensitive nature of an English Setter, that is understandable. He is most comfortable with women and has a bit of a watch dog and retreat mentality, which means he will always bark when there is a car in the driveway or someone at the door. He often barks when his foster Dad enters the room where he is with his foster Mom, so any men in the home would have to be gentle and patient. No kids because of this anxiety and his desire for a calm home.

Rocky loves to snuggle and wiggles his gratitude for any attention. He is very excited on leash and pulls like a draft horse. He needs a strong and steady person to work on his leash skills with him. He would not be good in a home with elderly people. He needs a home with a fenced yard that is interesting for a Setter. Having the opportunity for regular exercise is key to Rocky's long-term happiness and health. He has moderate hip dysplasia, which is common for our breed, does not require surgery and does not slow him down one bit. He will be fine with 4 foot fencing.

One of Rocky's most distinctive features is how intensely he looks straight into your eyes and seems to ask "will you love me?" The person who says "yes" will have a fantastic new friend and companion for life if they are just patient with him.

Rocky is neutered, up to date on vaccines and tests, microchipped, and on heartworm preventative. He is in a foster home in Boerne, TX and is available for adoption in the Texas area.
 ?.  

For an application to adopt or for more information about Southwest English Setter Rescue including our adoption requirements and transport availability, please go to http://www.swesr.org/. Please call us at 214-997-3885 if you have any questions.

*** DUE TO COVID-19, WE ARE NOT HAVING OUR NORMAL ADOPTION EVENTS.  MEET AND GREET IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY.  EMAIL, STAFF@ARVSIMI.ORG, WITH CONTACT NUMBER AND CITY YOU RESIDE.  PLEASE BE PATIENT AS WE NAVIGATE THESE UNCHARTED WATERS.   We DO NOT adopt out of state. ***

Annie was born in approximately 2013.  She is a very sweet, affectionate dog who gets along with all other dogs.  She is mostly potty trained with the occasional accident.  She has had some tooth loss, and several teeth pulled at last dental.  We generally soak her kibble to make it easier for her to chew.  Annie is currently about 14.5 pounds.

Annie was rescued from the shelter.  Her owner had moved and left her with friends who did not want her so they passed her along to someone else, who also didn’t want her and they left her outside, so they didn’t have to deal with her.  Annie was good at escaping from their yard and would often be found wandering the neighborhood.  She was finally picked up by Animal Control and brought to the shelter.  Owners were contacted and relinquished Annie to the shelter.  It was then discovered that Annie had a severe heart murmur that would need to be evaluated by a veterinary cardiologist.  Annie’s foster mom noticed Annie having frequent episodes that looked similar to seizures but were later diagnosed as heart disease.  Annie has a left Atrium leaky valve and an enlarged heart, which has been managed well with medication.  She will need to remain on this medication for the rest of her life, and have regular follow up visits with a cardiologist to monitor her progress.  Annie also takes a prescription Apoquel for seasonal allergies.

animal.description:
Luca is AN EXAMPLE OF AN IG in foster care in Los Angeles County.   He is a "senior" at between 13-14 years old. HE IS NOT UP FOR ADOPTION.

We don’t know much about Luca’s life before he came into Rescue but we do know he suffered many years of abuse and neglect.  Luca was found as a stray; his physical condition was very poor the result of living outside without shelter, food or basic care.   Of all the things we do not know about Luca we do know one, very important thing about him…. his will to live.  Luca has overcome his physical challenges and is now healthy and thriving.  He appreciates every day and finds joy in being a “house-hound”…..  his favorite place in the house is his foster mom’s bed.  He snuggles with her every night and loves to burrow in blankets.   According to Luca, a dog can “never have too many blankets”.  It has been our job in Rescue to not only provide him with the medical support and care he needed to get healthy but to insure he never again is without a safe place to live and that he always has as many blankets as he wants.

Luca’s on-going medical care is minimal, he takes Hepato Support, an Rx supplement (milk thistle) that strengthens his liver; he is also on a soft , fresh food diet made by the Fresh Pet company.   We would like his permanent home to continue using both of these items.

Luca is a little shy when meeting new humans but he is very comfortable with other dogs; having a dog companion in his new home would be helpful.  Luca does need assistance with learning some basic dog skills such as walking on leash.  He has shown a bit of fear and associates a leash with a negative experience.   He will go outside to potty if someone goes with him or if the door remains open so he knows he can come back inside and won’t be left outside.     

For Luca to continue to evolve and thrive we feel that his new home should have someone who can be home with him to help guide and encourage him to overcome his uncertainesses and to help him feel safe in his new surroundings.  Someone who is experienced working with Rescue Dogs would be beneficial.  A dog friend in the family and having a bit of secure outdoor space to potty will help him make a successful transition from orphan to family member.
animal.name: Luca

He is energetic, loves to explore and go on walks or runs. He is affectionate and playful with people he trusts, weighs 40 to 45 pounds, and is all muscle! The ultimate companion once he chooses his humans, he loves to play fetch, have belly rubs and tolerates his baths very well! He is protective, and does love to patrol his area, so a securely fenced yard is a must for him. New people will need to let him come to you - approaching his human or his fence isn't a good idea unless he's certain the approaching person is a good human (he is a product of animal abuse and understandably leery of strangers). BJ enjoys getting all of the attention; and would need a meet and greet with any potential fur-siblings.

His adoption fee has been lovingly sponsored by one of our wonderfully supportive friends of animals. Please fill out an adoption application at our website - stoveranimalrescue.com - and make an appointment to come meet BJ!

Foster Homes Needed!

Do you have time and room in your life for a foster dog?

http://www.muttloverescue.org/foster.html

*****************

Jethro had a temporary foster who says he is a good boy and is a people oriented dog. He is very sweet and loves toys and belly rubs. This guy is such a goofball and pretty sure there isn't anything he doesn't love, want to be friends with, or receive love from. Jethro is around 2-3 years old and is 60 pounds. Jethro is itching for a couch & a family to call his own

**BECAUSE OF OUR REQUIREMENT FOR A HOME VISIT, WE ARE ONLY ABLE TO ADOPT TO HOMES IN THE NORTHERN VA / MARYLAND / DC METRO AREA**

We have adoption events EVERY SATURDAY from 12-3 p.m. Please note that not all dogs can attend every event, so if you are interested in meeting a particular dog, please complete a no-obligation application on our website at http://www.muttloverescue.org/application.html OR write to adopt@muttloverescue.org.

Upcoming adoption events:

Mutt Love Rescue is doing everything we can to ensure the health and safety of our volunteers and adopters while continuing our mission to find homes for as many dogs as possible.

Effective immediately, we will not be holding our weekly adoption events. Dogs available for adoption can be met by appointment only. Potential adopters should submit an online application at http://muttloverescue.org/application.html. Once we receive your application, we will contact you to let you know the next steps.

We are always desperate for foster homes, now more than ever. If you are interested in fostering during this difficult time, please complete an application... unless you are a previous adopter/foster, then you can just contact us via phone (703-988-2608) or email (adopt@muttloverescue.org) to tell us which dog you want to foster!

For information on sponsoring this dog, please write to adopt@muttloverescue.org.

WE NEED FOSTER HOMES! FOR MORE INFORMATION, PLEASE EMAIL ADOPT@MUTTLOVERESCUE.ORG.

Visit us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/muttloverescue
Follow us on Twitter: @Muttlove_Rescue

animal.description:
Zorro is looking for his person and being one of the longest residents at the shelter, he can't wait to find his furever home! He is a 70 lb., four-year-old shepherd mix - we actually had him DNA tested and his results were quite interesting! Surprisingly, Zorro is 25% German Shepherd, 25% Catahoula Leopard, 25% American Staffordshire Terrier, 12.5% Boxer and 12.5% other. What a combo! 

This handsome boy enjoys being active, spending time outside hiking or playing, and going on adventures. He loves to run around the yard but also enjoys cuddling on the couch. He already knows basic commands and is very smart! He takes treats gently and would be a highly motivated student for more training.  

Zorro will require an experienced adult-only home as an only pet. Adopters that will provide further enrichment, training, and exercise are a must. If you can open your heart and give this special dog the family he deserves, please email dogs@daws.org to set up an appointment to meet him.

Check Zorro out here: https://www.facebook.com/118446594853659/posts/2684473841584242?vh=e&d=n&sfns=mo

animal.description:
MEET QUINCY

Quincy was hit by a car and layed in the ditch and was thought to be dead.

The same lady that spotted him the day before drove by him again and noticed his head move up and down and stopped to help. She gave him some water and called the police.

The police called some rescuers that called us and asked if we could help! ABSOLUTELY!!!

He was a matted mess and his eyes were matted shut. They groomed him down we did x-rays and he had a fractured pelvis. 

He is completely healed up and doing well and available for adoption!!

He is a sweet boy that deserves a new life!

Quincy is 10-11 years old.

EMAIL:
mini-mutts@outlook.com

TO APPLY- Your dog’s heartworm prevention and testing must be seen on vet records or other proof must be included. The records must show 2 years of continuous prevention.
Your application will not be approved without this documentation.

(fosters/adopters must be in the Dallas/Fort Worth/Rockwall or surrounding area only)

ONE WEEK HOME TRIAL BEFORE ADOPTING
NO CHILDREN UNDER 5YRS
NO LARGE DOGS

animal.description:
Please note: Rocky is being fostered in the Twin City area so his adopter will need to be from this area as well. Several meet and greets will be required before adoption.

Rocky is a 4-year-old, 55-pound Golden Retriever who came to RAGOM when his loving family did not have the time to handle his behavioral needs.

He is a typical Golden who craves human contact and would do best with a family who is home most of the time and doesn't travel much. If you do travel, he'd love to come along--he enjoys car rides!

Due to his resource-guarding tendencies, Rocky must be placed in an adult-only home with a physical fence and he cannot live with any other pets. His family must also be diligent about keeping human things out of his reach and allow him to play with his toys undisturbed.

Rocky is crate trained and walks well with a Gentle Leader. Continued training will be crucial for a successful adoption. He has learned so much in foster care and demonstrates great potential!

Finally, Rocky requires a lot of exercise to burn off his high energy. If you're a runner, hiker, or cross-country skier, Rocky will fit nicely into your exercise routine.

To learn more about Rocky, see his bio at: https://ragom.org/dogs/rocky-18-007

Placement Requirements:
Good With Dogs: No
Good With Cats: No
Good With Kids:  No 
Fence: Physical fence required
Age: 4

If you are interested in any of the dogs available at Retrieve a Golden of the Midwest (RAGOM), you can read our adoption process and apply to adopt, which can be found at https://ragom.org/our-adoption-process. RAGOM’s adoption territory includes: Minnesota; Iowa; North Dakota; South Dakota; Western Wisconsin (within 75 miles of the Minnesota border)

animal.description:
LOVES older kids but no other pets

Meet our Lilly Bloom, a 2-3-year-old  spayed female sweet girl who loves kids, but is not good with other pets. We think Lilly is a mixture of American Staffordshire terrier and French bulldog. She weighs about 30 lb.
 
Lilly needs an only-pet home with a fenced yard and some bigger kids to play with. She is very sweet and needs exercise. She would love to have obedience training and perhaps agility training or be a running partner.She will also need a refresher on house-training because she has been in boarding (no foster homes available).
 
Lilly is up-to-date on vaccines, heart worm negative and microchipped along with being spayed. She has a slight  under-performing thyroid and takes a supplement each day, but this is not an expensive medication.
 
To find out more about Lilly Bloom, call her buddy, Kelli, at 803-646-2593. She is currently in South Carolina. Lilly's adoption fee is $175. Transportation north is available at a very reasonable cost.

animal.description:
Vance is a handsome boy and NEEDS A FOSTER HOME!!
House trained
Vance is a Golden/Pyrenees mix and he is just a beautiful boy who desperately needs a foster home!!
He’s not happy in the kennel and we can’t blame him as it’s kind of crazy at times with lots of barking going on – and we have a lot of dogs right now!
He will curl up on your lap and jump on your bed if you let him?. He loves ‘his people’, which right now is the kennel staff and volunteers.

You won’t have to worry about squirrels or chipmunks in your yard as he’ll chase them off for sure!

He definitely needs an experienced adult household, with no kids under 16, and an above ground fenced yard (no apartments). Vance is not a real social dog as he likes to be at home with his people and he likes his walks.

Can anyone take this sweet boy out of the kennel?

He likes smaller dogs but he is not wild about larger dogs and no cats. This sweet boy likes walks around the park and walks fine on leash. While he was out and about at the kennel, he wanted lots of loving in the office!!! And… Vance Loves fetching toys!
We are still learning about this cutie, but if you would like to meet him and get him out of the kennel, please contact GRRAND ASAP!
At this time, we are unable to process any applications that are outside of the geographic areas listed below:
Greater Louisville, KY (including adjacent southern Indiana)
Greater Lexington, KY
Southern Indiana Counties:  Clark and Floyd
Ohio Counties: Hamilton, Butler, Warren, some areas within Clermont county, Montgomery and Green
Northern KY Counties: Boone, Kenton and Campbell
 
To inquire about a specific dog, we require that you first submit an adoption application.  Visit http://grrand.org/online-adoption-application/  to access our online application.  You do not need to fill out an application for each dog you are interested in learning more about.  Once your application is reviewed a GRRAND volunteer will contact you to begin the process.  Our Adoption Placement Coordinator will work with you to find a dog with the characteristics to best fit your family.

I can be very picky about what other doggy friends I like. I do have a high prey drive so I would be best in a home without small animals. I would do best in an only dog home or with and experienced owner willing to work at me living with another dog. Definitely no small dogs, cats or other pets. I am vision impaired although that doesn’t stop my prey drive as my sniffer works perfectly well. I

Xo, Jiao

-Up-to-date vaccinations
-Spay/neuter
-Microchip & microchip registration

The adoption process requires an initial approved Adoption Application, a home visit to ensure safety and well-being of adoptee & a separate Adoption Agreement.

**Adoption fees vary and are NOT NEGOTIABLE. 

NOTE: An Adoption Application does not guarantee an adoption. Adoptions are based on the best possible situation for each dog and their prospective owners. Not all breeds are right for all people and not all people are right for all breeds. Our commitment is to place these animals in the right homes so that they never again have to face re-homing. They deserve a forever family too.

Additionally, each adoption includes a one week, partial fee refundable, trial period to ensure pet is a right fit.

NO OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS

animal.description:
"Dobby has no master. Dobby is a free dog."

As a foster mom, I'd love to share with you a very special soul. Dobby's name is Dobby for a reason. He comes to rescue after a very abused past which led him to roam and hide for many months in southern MO. I'm not sure which is worse to imagine, his terror he once went through or the horribly embedded collar Dobby had prior to having it surgically removed. The images are too graphic to share but if you look into his eyes and see something there, we will expose how Dobby entered into rescue. For now, I want to share with you how much Dobby has grown in personality and all of his qualities.

Dobby has been in rescue since early February 2019. In little time, a fully feral dog, that shivered at the sight and touch of a human, he has come a long way. Dobby has learned, at least in his current setting, how to be a dog. A dog that shares space with other dogs (little to big, male and female); a dog that seeks affection and touch from humans (mainly women at this point); a dog that cuddles in bed every night or on the couch because he can; a dog that plays, rough-houses, and learns new things because it's fun and treats are wonderful; and a dog that found his voice, because what cattledog doesn't! Truth is, it wasn't just a patient, soft human that taught him these things - it was his fur-family as well. Dobby needs a patient and friendly fur-member to keep that spark in his eyes and share the confidence.

Dobby's ideal home setting would be patient, kind, positive, have a very secure, privacy fenced yard (likely not a chain link- it is too easy for him to be tempted to jump in a moment of scare), have another dog as sort of his guide, and for now, at least a human mom that will help ease him into a new home, setting and continue teaching him. Dobby is housebroken and crate trained and is very food motivated. Dobby takes treats gently from your hand and will continue gaining trust with people with some home exercises involving treats/food and hand feeding. He's also quite the talker! Loves to yoddle and approach for affection.

Dobby fears alpha dogs and would not do well paired with one. He likely isn't going to be an easy companion to take on a hike, as attaching a leash to his collar (even for a vet visit) is still very traumatic for him. In time, this can change but will take practice and positive encouragement. However, for the right family, Dobby could start his journey. He has met a lot of new people - from families coming over to visit and pick their newest member from a foster litter of puppies, to normal guests/neighbors and even the dog sitter. However, due to Dobby's unpredictable leash behavior, walks and outdoor events are not really his thing.

If you or your family see what loving soul he has to offer and up for a challenge, I know the loyalty and love he can share will bring mutual gain. Please submit an adoption application which helps us answer the most basic of questions to see if there's a potential connection between you and Dobby!

animal.description:
Roscoe’s early years were not happy. When he came to Underdog, he was so fearful he couldn't even walk across the room without cringing, and he spent almost a month living in his exercise pen by the front door, coming out only for walks.  He didn't trust people and growled and snapped frequently.  He has gradually come out of his shell and as you can see by his pictures, is very loving and craves attention.  He still has a long way to go. He does not like to be picked up, and is easily startled by sudden movements or noises. He gets along well with the foster dogs he lives with, but reacts aggressively to any new dogs that come to visit. He is looking for a quiet home, no cats, guinea pigs, hamsters, etc., no small children.  He has always loved to go for walks, but must be on a secure leash as he will lunge at strange dogs and people.  He will need time to adjust to a new home, and will be fearfully aggressive during the transition, so must have someone who understands and is comfortable managing this behavior. He has a history of partial seizures and takes medication twice a day to keep them under control.  Adoption fee is $125.


PS you can see videos of me on Underdog Rescue of Florida Facebook

All UnderDogs are spayed/neutered, heartworm checked, microchipped, up to date on vaccines and heartworm/flea/tick preventatives.  For consideration for one or more dogs, we require that an on-line application is filled out.  Go to www.UnderdogAdopt.com for our application.  Sorry, we do not adopt outside of Florida.  Applicants are subject to a home visit, and veterinary references will be checked. Please include a vet reference (including phone number) when applying online.
Our application process:
FIRST, an application must be approved for adoption from our rescue.
SECOND, we determine whether the dog that has been applied for is a "good match" for the household that wants to adopt him/her.  We take into consideration the dog's activity level, compatibility with other members of the household (human and other pets), etc.
If your application has been approved, but the dog you applied for is no longer available, please take the time and look over our adoptable dogs again.  We will make every effort to find the right dog for an approved applicant.
We hope you agree and understand that our goal to find the best forever home is our #1 priority!

animal.description:
Jayne is a sweet 5-year-old girl. She is bouncy and energetic and would love an active home. Jayne loves going for walks in her harness and loves to run and play ball in our fenced pen. She is not an apartment dog and will need someone who will walk her on leash or who has a fenced yard. Jayne can be reactive when cornered and has run loose in the past, so for her safety, she should not be let off-leash. 

Jayne would do best in an adult only home with no children and no cats. She enjoys wrestling and playing with other dogs, especially with her son Buddy (who is at the shelter and needs a home) and has some patented wrestling moves. While Jayne enjoys playing with other dogs it is important for her to have a proper introduction to any new dogs. Any dogs in the home will need to come meet Jayne before adoption to make sure the dogs are compatible. 

Jayne can be nervous around new people, but if you go slow, she becomes super lovey-dovey, enjoys giving hugs, and loves having her belly rubbed. Jayne is generally more comfortable with women and would either like a home without men or a home where the men are gentle and patient, giving her lots of personal space and allowing her to come to them on her terms so she can learn to trust them with time.

If you are interested in adopting this sweet girl, please start by filling out an adoption application that can be found on our website at trilakeshumanesociety.org or give us a call at 518-891-0017 if you would like a hard copy mailed to you. Once we have an approved adoption application we can set up an appointment for you to come in and meet Jayne, spend some time with her, and see if she is a good fit for you and your household.

animal.description:
Andy is a fun, energetic guy who loves nothing more than to stretch his legs and RUN. We think he is a mix between Border Collie and Whippet.

He requires an adult only home with a securely fenced, and large yard where he can get his zoomies out, or simply spend the afternoon lounging in the sun. He would not do well in an apartment or a condo. 

Andy is crate trained and has all of his obedience. He walks beautifully on a leash, knows how to run alongside of a bike and loves to explore nature and go hiking in the woods with his people. 

Andy requires daily exercise - even if that simply means throwing a toy in the yard. While he relaxes well inside, he can become anxious if he doesn’t have a way to stretch his legs regularly. 

Andy has undergone extensive training, and he would do best with an owner willing to continue reinforcing what he knows. Follow up training is provided free of charge within the Sequim/Port Angeles areas.

He can get overexcited very easily, when doing things like meeting new people, or greeting those he really loves, so he’d benefit from owners willing to help him practice calm, appropriate behavior. Andy would enjoy a canine companion that is balanced, calm and can be a mentor to him, as well as a play mate.

Andy requires a special, high calorie diet, and daily supplements which will be provided. 

Visit our website to fill out an Adoption Application  http://www.wagsequimwa.com. Adoption donation $400.

Please contact Claudia at claudiaatwag@gmail.com for more information.

animal.description:
Brownie is a sweetheart with a strong spirit!

Brownie has had a really rough few years and is ready for a lifetime of love.  She first came to FFL after being mistreated by her owner and taken in by a wonderful neighbor, and then went home with a loving foster. She had a history of isolation and neglect, but she is now on the path to recovery and is ready to find a forever home.

Brownie is learning! Brownie is a smart dog who learns fast.  She knows to sit, down, stay, leave it, and off, and is working on shake. She is well behaved in the crate and kennel and is house-trained. Strong and sturdy, she sometimes tugs on her leash and could still use some work to master loose leash walking. 

Brownie loves to play!  Brownie has energy and loves to play and run around.  She would thrive in a house with a yard for her to run around in while supervised. She would do best in a home willing to provide her with healthy outlets for her mind and energy. A home without many visitors would also be ideal. 

Brownie needs patience!  Brownie is still trying to figure out what it means to be a well-loved pet.  She enjoys cuddles on her terms and is a very loving dog.  Prior to being taken in by her neighbor, she had never been shown affection and is still learning how to ask for snuggles. 

Brownie has all the potential in the world to be the best dog ever.  She is loyal, loving, and energetic.  She would do well in a home willing to be patient while working with her through training.  She is ready to heal from her rough past and live the rest of her life surrounded by love and happiness.  Apply to meet her today!

animal.description:
Nala has a heart of gold to match her golden coat!

Nala is ready and waiting to shower you with her love! She is the perfect companion and everything you could ask for in a doggy soulmate.  She is affectionate, smart, goofy, and - most importantly - waiting for her forever home! 

Nala is well-rounded! She would make a great companion for any adventure you want to take her on. Nala loves car rides, either in her crate or safely secured in the back seat, and is happy to go on long drives with her family.  She loves to do whatever her humans are doing, whether than means going on a stroll, a hike, or relaxing on the couch.  She is easily excitable and has never been around cats or young children for that reason but she loves playing with dogs of a similar energy level.  She is wonderful at sharing toys and treats with other dogs and her humans but she’s working on sharing her food.

Nala is a genius! She is super smart and eager to please her humans which means that she loves to learn new things.  So far, she is crate-trained, house-trained, and walks well on a leash.  She knows “Sit”, “Lay Down”, “Load Up”, and is currently working on “Wait”.  She is a high-energy pup and would do best in a home with a yard but could adapt to an apartment with the right amount of mental and physical stimulation. 

Nala is the best cuddler in town!  She is super affectionate and wants to be a lapdog.  Her size is just right for her to snuggle up in your lap or by your side.  She enjoys sleeping in bed with her favorite people and likes to spend her days following her humans from room to room.  

Nala is an intelligent, silly, sweet dog with a personality that shines.  Her bubbly demeanor is contagious and her goofy antics and warm cuddles will put a smile on your face every day.  Nala is looking for a forever home that can work with her energy level and give her lots of love.  Apply to meet her today.

animal.description:
Dipper is as precious as they come, but can she can also be a lot to handle. That might be partly because she was thrown out of a car and tried to chase her people down. Since then, her biggest desire is to have someone of her own to love.

Dipper would do best with someone who has experience with a high energy dog and understands that she needs LOTS of exercise, stimulation and interaction, and who can laugh off the crazy antics of a high energy dog. She does best when she exercises before training and loves to play fetch. She really loves listening for direction and applying her smarts.

Though she is high energy, she really is super sweet, and just wants nothing more than to be loved.

Dipper is dog selective. She gets along great with certain dogs but not all.


Adoption Fees:
Kittens: $60, Cats (1 year plus): $50, Puppies: $250, Adult Canines (1 to 6 years): $200, Seniors (7 years plus): $100 (unless otherwise specified). Adoption fees are not a tax-deductible donation as allowed by IRS regulations. Adoption fees help to offset the cost of the pet's care incurred by Coastal Pet Rescue, which are generally 2 to 3 times the adoption fee amount.
Some special circumstances may change the fee; see pet's listing for actual adoption fee.

All Coastal Pet Rescue pets are current on shots, microchipped* and spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Adopters are responsible for any shots that may be due after adoption (particularly for kittens and puppies that must have three rounds of shots to be protected).

Microchip:
CPR has implanted a microchip as part of the adoption process and the chip is included in the adoption fee. However, some chip companies require a registration fee varying from $9.99 to $19.99. The registration fees are the responsibility of the adopter and are NOT included in the CPR adoption fee. Adopters may add this cost to their adoption fee to have CPR register the chip on their behalf.

30 Days Pet Insurance: 
As a Petfinder member, all adopters are entitled to a free 30 day insurance policy through PetFirst. Coastal Pet Rescue is not responsible for this policy. Adopters must call PetFirst’s toll-free number 855-710-7387 to activate the coverage. If adopters fail to call, the policy will not be activated.

animal.description:
Good With Kids: Yes Good With Other Dogs: Yes Good With Cats: No House trained: Yes Crate Trained: Yes Walks Nicely On A Leash: Yes Knows Basic Commands: Successfully completed Training classes Energy Level (Couch Potato, Moderate or High): Moderate to High Special Needs: due to her anxiety she is on medications that help calm her, she will need medications long term Arrival story: We found Tater at Macomb County AC. She arrived as a stray. Approximate Age / Weight: 3 Years Old and 45 lbs. Personality: Tater Tot has come a long way since she's been in foster care. She can be unsure when meeting new people, particularly men. We’ve watched her blossom and make strides in her confidence in foster care, but we are still working on her confidence around men. At this time, Tater requires a quiet home with no adult males and not many visitors. This energetic girl would love a doggie playmate. She has a blast at dog daycare, so a home with another energetic dog is a bonus! Tater loves to play chase and romp with her dog friends during the day and will happily cozy up with a chew bone when everyone settles down at night. She's a super affectionate and cuddly girl with her people and those she knows. She’s also a graduated training class with flying colors! Forever Home: Tater would love to be part of an active family and, ideally, have an energetic canine pal. Though Tater is much better meeting new women, she still struggles when meeting new men. So, for her comfort, we are seeking a home without men. Our sweet girl would also do best in a quieter home without a lot of house guests or young children. No invisible fences for Tater, please.

Contact: Please contact wtdr2008@yahoo.com to adopt Tater!

Pre-Adoption Application:

To be considered for a dog, it is best to submit a pre-adoption application. The pre-adoption application can be downloaded from our website - www.waggintailsdogrescue.org/adoptionprocess.html. Just complete the application and email it back to wtdr2008@yahoo.com

Waggin' Tails Adoption Information:

Waggin' Tails Dog Rescue has a standard adoption fee of $225 for adult dogs. Different adoption fees apply for older dogs, small breeds and puppies - $125 for senior dogs (9 years +) , $275 for small breed dogs and $250 for puppies, plus a $50 deposit which is returned upon proof of spay/neuter. Our adoption process includes an application, vet reference checks, and a home visit.

Waggin' Tails Dog Rescue does not have a shelter facility. All of our dogs are fostered in private homes. To meet a dog in person, please see our event calendar on our website at www.waggintailsdogrescue.org for the latest information. Arrangements can be made to meet our rescue dogs outside of Saturday adoption events after an approved application is submitted. This application does not imply an obligation to adopt by the applicant or by the rescue group.

Our volunteers have made rescue a second job that they do in their spare time after coming home from full-time jobs. E-mail inquiries are the quickest way to obtain information about a dog.

Thank you for your support of rescue and your interest in a rescue dog!

animal.description:
Marcel seeks a LOCAL, ADULT only, cat free indoor home with a securely fenced back yard.Previous experience with dogs with behavioral issues is a must.

The Good

Marcel is a 4-6 year brindle French Bulldog rescued from local shelter after his stray hold was over. He is a larger chubby  Frenchie at around 42 lbs. Marcel is an extremely affectionate dog. He loves to play with toys. He loves to snuggle in blankets and wrap himself up like a burrito. He loves FOOD! He is super smart! He is great with other dogs as long as he is the boss dog, He walks well on the leash and likes rides in the car. He is a furniture dog! 

The Bad

Marcel does not do well with cats and should be in a cat free home. He can jump almost any babygate! As is often typical with bulldogs, Marcel may be prone to skin issues so a quality diet and regular flea prevention is a must. 

The Ugly

We do not know what happened in Marcel’s past, but it did kind of mess him up. Marcel is severely cage aggressive. He is not to be crated and if boarding is needed, a very savvy kennel will be required. 

Marcel also has some major boundary issues and when pushed is quite reactive. If pushed, he will likely bite. When he first came to foster care, he was terrified of going outside we suspect fearful of not being let back in and trying to make him go outside was not and option as he would react. At first we could trick him into going out about once a day. Since then he now goes out with the other dogs and will occasionally even ask to go but still he does not like to go out at night. Because of this we consider him about 74% housetrained and may still have an accident. While getting him to go outside has been where we have seen this most, he does react to other things as well. 

As, we said you absolutely cannot make Marcel do anything but if you can make him think it is his idea – all is good. 

The Rest

Marcel seeks an adult only, cat free indoor home with a securely fenced back yard. A dog door may address some of his issues though he may also refuse to even consider one. Previous experience with dogs with behavioral issues is a must. Marcel is safe and relatively well adjusted in his foster home but we would love to see if there is a more perfect fit for him and since we do not want to set him up to fail we will not settle for less than perfect! 

Marcel is neutered, current on vaccines, heartworm negative and on prevention and chipped. 

LOCAL INQUIRIES ONLY

I do well on car rides. I will love to follow you around and sitting in your lap. I am a real lover boy. Because I am blind I would not be good for an elderly person as I can be a trip hazard. Also I can’t go in a home with a swimming pool or small children. My foster parents think I am the greatest foster EVER! Please come by and see me in person. Copy and paste this URL link to learn everything you need to know about the adoption process and to fill out the application.
https://www.grandstrandhumanesociety.com/adopt/

Gage has been in a foster home for quite some time and while he has generated a lot of interest the right forever home has not been found for him yet. 

He would not do well in home with cats or children. As you can see from his photos he has a soft side and is a goof ball. He loves other dogs but is dog selective. He will be the alpha dog.  His story is a long sad one. He was trained horribly, the old chain em up and tease and tortured until he bit. Then he was brought to us and dropped off. Shortly after, hurricane Florence was hitting SC and the shelter was evacuated.  Once we returned to the shelter, we noticed that he had chewed his back foot nearly to the bone likely due to the stress of evacuation. He was taken in by an experienced foster to be treated and go through rehab. It took 9 months to heal. 
He will need an owner who understands the breed and who can be firm with him. He is a rescue, they are not flawless. 
Because he’s in a foster home a meet and greet will be scheduled once it’s determined that an adopter is possibly a good fit for Gage. If you think you are the right person to give this beautiful boy a home and would like to speak to Gage’s foster family to learn more about him please contact our Enrichment Counselor, James. He can be reached on his cell number 410-533-8676.

animal.description:
Sahara is a beautiful 4-1/2 year old spayed female who was previously a Pittie Paw Rescue Dog and has had a rough past.  Guardians for the Animals of Ohio Rescue pulled her from Knox Animal Shelter after she was seized from the former Rescue.   

Her foster has this to say about this amazing girl: 

I know of multiple homes she was in and they didn’t give her a chance, didn’t work with her and didn’t devote enough time to her. She’s had urine burns at one point, dog fights at another, close to being euthanized at the shelter and she’s just been all around let down. She is one of the best girls ever, for most people. She does occasionally leash bite but with a constant reminder and harnesses, she has the potential to do really well. She is fairly calm on her own, she doesn’t approve of being in a crate but can be left out unattended if needed. We prefer to house her in a heavy duty crate.

 

She does have potential to be with another dog with very slow, steady intros but due to multiple attack’s in the past.. she’s slow to trust other dogs. She is really good with cats and absolutely adores children. She can go for walks without reacting to other dogs but enjoys her person overall. She is house trained and a complete cuddle expert.....she will never let you down with company for a night in. She’s been let down so many times in the past and it shocks me how when she’s truly a good girl. She knows multiple commands and is eager to learn more. She’s very treat motivated as well.

 

She is really just looking for her forever place to crash, with someone who won’t give up on her.  If interested in more information please contact Guardians for the Animals of Ohio Rescue or fill out an adoption application to meet Sahara.

Brownie is a super sweet, energetic, affectionate Staffy/Bulldog mix who is about 5 years old and weighs 47 lbs. She is a very smart girl who knows basic commands and enjoys being the best dog she can be!  Her house manners are impeccable and she rarely barks. She takes treats gently from your hand, knows basic commands, and walks well on a leash. She rarely barks, but often makes a cute snorting sound that always brings a smile to our faces! Brownie is housebroken, crate trained, spayed, fully vaccinated & microchipped. She was heartworm positive, but the shelter advocates raised the funds needed to treat her. She has completed her HW treatment and is ready now to find her loving, forever home! Brownie has received professional training  thru US Canine in Buford and comes with a lifetime of ongoing training with them if necessary." 

For more information about Brownie, please email us at info@barkvilledogrescue.org. If you would like to adopt sweet Brownie,  please submit your application for her at http://www.barkvilledogrescue.org/adoption-application.

animal.description:
To access the home page for our group, click on Southern Comfort Maltese Rescue which will take you to the map page.  Below the map is our logo and the link to click on to access adoption forms, contact info or to donate. ALL DONATIONS ARE TAX DEDUCTIBLE.


Adoption Fee:  $100.00

 
Roccoboy is a precious little fella who is 11 years old and weighs about 8 pounds.  His family was no longer able to care for him, so he came to SCMR.

He is a wonderfully sweet boy; however, he has a collapsing trachea that we are monitoring and luxating patellas' in both knees. He is not a candidate for surgery as his kneecaps are now frozen inward causing him to walk bowlegged.  He has lost all but 4 of his teeth but does well eating wet food and kibble that has been softened. 

He also has environmental allergies.  We have learned that he is highly allergic to Febreze, so any home adopting him will have to agree to not use that product in the home.  Febreze comes in candles, spray bottles, wall plug ins, Gain laundry detergent, liquid laundry softer, and it is also in kitchen garbage bags.  Febreze causes him to break out with skin sores and scratches constantly when he has been exposed. 

Roccoboy also has an extremely enlarged heart  The veterinarian can only hear a slight murmur, but the x-rays show his heart is very large.

He is partially house trained, being able to use peepads most of the time, but he is not willing to venture outside for any reason, preferring to stay inside.  He is not one to want to snuggle and sit with his humans, preferring to use his doggie bed to nap for a lot of the day.

Roccoboy should be the only dog in the home.  He may get along with larger pets but does seem to have issues with and will fight smaller dogs.  There are no cats in the home so it is unknown how he would be with them. 

This cutie is relaxing in Gainesville, FL until he is adopted.  He is loved and being well cared for in his foster home, being included as part of the family.


NOTE: SCMR DOES NOT adopt to homes with children under the age of 10 years or homes with Electric Fences

Out-of-state adoptions are possible; however, the approved adoptive home is responsible for making the necessary arrangements to pick up their new little one.

animal.description:
Everyone should have a friend who will tell you if you have spinach in your teeth.  Or, just hypothetically, if you have an ear out of place while a picture is being taken. I'm Zoe and I need a friend like that! 

I'm a 7-year-old mixed breed girl and have been learning all kinds of great things lately. I love my toys and I'm a great athlete. I have also been rocking the basic obedience classes, which will help me be a perfectly poised pooch when I go home with you! I'm super selective about my four-legged dog friends and appreciate a slow introduction, but being an only dog in my new home would be best. 

Part of my training is learning to trust people, which is awesome because they use treats to get to know me better. And, to be honest, I am pretty happy getting treats and might be working this angle just a bit!

I also have a unique skill -- I can hold not just one, not just two, not even just three, but FOUR tennis balls in my mouth! Go me! 

Do you think you might be my person, the friend person who will adjust my ear before I have a photo taken? The one who will love me and appreciate my remarkable self? The one who will give me time to trust and feed me treats? 

If you think we might be good together, please text or call The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387 for more information about me. 

*Zoe is spayed, vaccinated, microchipped, and ready for her home. She's staying in the Kansas City metro area, but transport is available to the right home. She's eligible for a no-cost adoption with an encouraged donation. 

INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS PET? Fill out an Adoption Application now! Appointments can also be made to meet a pet by calling us at 913-671-PETS (913-671-7387).  

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
Prior to adoption, our animals are: 
**Tested for diseases 
**Vaccinated 
**Spayed/neutered 
**Microchipped 

NO COST adoptions with an encouraged donation are accepted. 

The Pet Connection also offers adopters a FREE veterinary examination and a medical care support plan for 60 days after adoption, as well as lifetime behavioral training, safe sanctuary for pets returned in emergency situations, extensive assistance with lost and found pets, and other expert pet services in a variety of areas, including pet selection, behavioral issues, general training, nutrition, and transition to adoptive homes.

Please visit our website at www.thepetconnection.org for more information about The Pet Connection and for a full listing of our available pets, 

Call or text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387 if you can foster, adopt, or sponsor a special needs dog or cat!

NOT AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION

Talullah came to Save the Dalmatians as an 8 week old  puppy in August 2017.  In addition to being deaf, it was found that she had 2 serious heart conditions and we initially did not think she would survive. However over time she continued to grow and act like any other dog. We brought her to a cardiologist where it was found that the two heart conditions are actually what is keeping her alive. One counter acts the other. 

Tallulah is part of our Forever Foster Program for dogs that are not likely to be adopted.  We find wonderful foster homes willing to foster for the life of the dog while we provide financial support for medical/veterinary needs.  These are wonderful dogs who through no fault of there own are unable to find permanent homes in a timely manner; usually due to age, medical and/or special needs.

Twice a year she sees the cardiologist for a check up and evaluation of her prescription medicines.  Talullah is being permanently fostered by one of our 2 time adopters, who has deaf dalmatian experience.  


To sponsor/donate via PayPal use our email address rescue@savethedals.org

If you prefer to mail us your donation please email us at info@savethedals.org.

Thank you

animal.description:
I'm Grimm, a very handsome 2 year old 8lb small mixed breed boy. I'm looking for someone experienced in VERY timid/FERAL dogs. I came from a home where there were 40 dogs. When I was just a puppy, I peed in the house and my human Dad picked me up by my neck, opened the door, and threw me as far as he could. Right then and there, I've never felt safe in this world.
     Then, my human Mom moved out and took us, but with nowhere to go, we were all living in a truck so she gave me to a nice rescue where they love me and promise to never let anyone hurt me again. It takes me a while to warm up to women, (I probably won't ever trust men AT ALL) but once I trust you I LOVE to just be in your lap as much as possible. I get along with other small dogs, but prefer not to share my new Mom with but maybe just 1 or 2 dogs at most, cats are ok too. I REQUIRE a 6 ft fence with absolutely no spaces for me to escape (if I were to get out you'd most likely never catch me) If you want to find out more about me, CALL (757) 432-9222.

animal.description:
Good with dogs: Yes
Good with cats: No
Good with kids: No
Crate trained: Yes
House trained: Mostly

Heavens Tabetsy (who goes by Tabby) is one of the sweetest and most affectionate dogs you will ever meet. She is also one of the shyest, as she gets very scared around new people and places. Tabbys first instinct is to run away from what she is scared of, but if that is not an option, she will freeze and occasionally go to the bathroom out of fear. However, once she is comfortable with you, Tabby acts like a normal playful puppy and will shower you with kisses and cuddles!

Tabby takes a few hours to warm up to a new person and about a week to become fully comfortable. She gets very attached to her people and tries to stay as close as possible around the house. She loves attention and will remind you with some hilariously uncoordinated pawing! Tabby is very playful and absolutely loves other pups! She is most comfortable around other dogs, and she will need a home with at least one confident pup to help show her the ropes. When she is not playing, Tabby is very calm inside and will relax next to her person or in her crate. The crate is her safe space and she is always happy to spend time there. Tabby is fully leash trained and is looking for an adopter who will continue to expose her to new situations. She might never warm up immediately to new people, but she is already making great progress learning that the world is not so scary! Tabby is a special girl, and if you give her time to warm up, the affection and gratitude she gives in return will make you fall madly in love.

Age: 3 years
Weight: 50 lbs.

Please Note: All dogs are posted until they are officially adopted. This dog may have other interested adopters in line. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website at www.lasthopek9.org.

Questions? Please email adoptions@lasthopek9.org. For more photos, or information on upcoming adoption events where you can meet her, please go to www.lasthopek9.org or go to our Facebook page. Thank you for your interest in saving a life!

animal.description:
Bolt is a year old deaf Australian Cattle Dog Mix. Bolt hails from the beautiful island of Kauai, Hawaii. He was flown to us by the local SPCA because great homes are in short supply on the island.
Bolt spent the first seven months of his life on a chain in the yard 24/7. Bored with no company and nothing to do, he resorted to digging and the landlord said he had to go.
Bolt is used to other dogs, and used to being around children. We're not sure about cats. He is a very energetic little guy, but he's also wicked smart. He graduated from our Beginners Group training class, and he LOVES to learn and work! He learns fast, and it lights him up with happiness.
Bolt is happy 24/7, and you can't look at him and not break out into a smile. He's a comedian and he loves to make people smile. He's super cute, both in looks and personality.
Bolt will need some patience, training and time to get used to the world around him. All he knew was a chain for most of his puppyhood, and our Ranch is a pretty quiet place.

To meet Bolt, please complete our online application for adoption: www.deafdogrescueofamerica.org/adoption-application.html

Please note that we are unable to respond to inquiries, emails or phone calls. Our adoption process starts with completion/submission of an application for adoption. All applications are reviewed as quickly as we can, and our adoption process is not first come, first served. We select our adoptive homes according to what our dogs/puppies require. If you are selected as an appropriate match, you will be contacted to set an appointment to visit the Ranch and meet Bolt.

animal.description:
Ricco is about  2  yrs old and weighs 52 lbs.   Ricco is about  2  yrs old and weighs 52 lbs.  Ricco aka Lucky is an energetic dog that needs to play, walk and run. He is curious and puppy-like and is happy-go-lucky, playful, and a little bit of a klutz. He likes to be around people and his tail is always wagging. He is friendly with family members, visitors, and kids (we have a six -year old).

Ricco aka Lucky needs basic house training and to learn commands. We have been working on potty training, but he is not yet house-broken. He has already learned to “sit” for meal service, and now willingly goes into his kennel when told “kennel”. He has been working on “come” and “stay”, but not quite there yet. He is motivated by treats. Lucky needs a patient family who can teach him all he needs to know about “house rules”. Lucky does well on a leash and does very well on walks. He is a great jumper, so if you keep any ball-shaped fruit on the counter, he will retrieve it and play ball; until he learns that counters are off-limits! (real-life situation!)

Lucky appears to be a great family dog due to his playful nature and would be a good guard dog due to his loyalty and human resource-guarding instinct.

Lucky is curious about other pets. We have a tortoise and a cat. He will bark at the cat and sniff the tortoise.  I believe Lucky would do well as an only pet. He will defend himself quite vigorously if threatened or attacked by another dog and will not easily give up.  More will be known about me soon.   

A Path 4 Paws holds adoption events EVERY Saturday & Sunday from 10am-4pm at C-A-L Ranch,  located at 232 N. Jones Blvd right off the I-95.   Please bring your dog(s) for a meet and greet (if applicable)

animal.description:
Duke is a beautiful brindle babe who has been searching for his forever family since3/19/2019.

Duke came to the shelter as an owner surrender due to no fault of his own. Duke was not being treated fairly by a small child in the home which left him broken and down. Since being at the shelter, Duke has shown that he can be a very sweet and loving boy once he gets to know you. With his past, Duke can be shy at first when meeting new people. Treat motivated, Duke loves to please and show off his obedience. Duke enjoys participating in play groups at the shelter as well as going on lunch runs to McDonalds.

Duke's forever family would consist of no small children, cats or other animals. This home will also include no children coming to visit the home due to his negative past experiences. As far as doggy siblings, Duke would prefer a more submissive playmate who will allow him to be the head honcho. Dog siblings will also be dependent on a meet and greet with an approved adopter. His forever family would ideally be home more than away and social butterflies need not apply! Duke's family will also need a fenced in yard to allow him to run and play as he pleases. 

Potential adopters will need to understand that they will partake in multiple meet and greets with Duke to allow him to become more comfortable and trusting. Staff recommends waiting at least 2 months at minimum until trying introductions with other adults, which would need to occur outside of the home. A breed experienced owner, with knowledge of slow intros and an understanding that Duke may never be a social butterfly will be preferred. 

 If interested in adopting Duke, please visit www.lebanonhumane.org for all the details on our current adoption process and application. Completed applications can be sent to info@lebanonhumane.org
